You&#39;ll need to find a replacement repository, or use the normal `rocksdbjni` dependency. Though to be clear, I don&#39;t know if that will work as I guess there was a special reason the Ethereum project released a separate artifact.

In any case, the normal RocksDB dependency is on Maven Central:

```xml
&lt;dependency&gt;
    &lt;groupId&gt;org.rocksdb&lt;/groupId&gt;
    &lt;artifactId&gt;rocksdbjni&lt;/artifactId&gt;
    &lt;version&gt;5.9.2&lt;/version&gt;
&lt;/dependency&gt;
```

(FYI, this is a version from 2018, the latest version at this time is 8.6.7 from 8 November 2023.)

  [1]: https://jfrog.com/blog/into-the-sunset-bintray-jcenter-gocenter-and-chartcenter/

